### **Executive Summary**
CMI Corporation’s Q3 2014 performance reveals material weaknesses in forward-looking financial transparency and earnings quality, undermining any attempt at fundamental valuation. While historical metrics demonstrate some resilience, the compounding absence of substantive guidance—coupled with management’s explicit downward revision to 2014 revenue and EBIT forecasts—signals deteriorating fundamentals. The lack of actionable strategic direction and unresolved earnings quality concerns (e.g., one-time costs) further exacerbate downside risk. Consequently, we adopt a **bearish stance** with **75% conviction**, recommending short positions across all time horizons until Q4 2014 guidance provides clarity on 2015 projections and operational initiatives.

